      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Court's Term Is Over, but Not the Discord; The Abortion Ruling</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Woodward letter criticizes Supreme Court ruling striking down state law banning 'partial-birth' abortion (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Court Rules That Governments Can't Outlaw Type of Abortion'' (front page, June 29):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Court Rules That Governments Can't Outlaw Type of Abortion'' (front page, June 29):</p>
        <p>I am profoundly saddened that our society has such disregard for the worth and dignity of human life. Partial-birth abortion cannot be distinguished from infanticide. It is a gruesome form of death, and the baby experiences extreme pain as his life comes to an abrupt and premature conclusion.</p>
        <p>History will judge our times as barbarous and uncivilized. Shame on you for applauding the court's decision (editorial, June 29).</p>
        <p>JOHN WOODWARD  Fort Kent, Me., June 29, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a Protestant minister.</p>
      </block>
